r bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utavaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tavaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/13/00 8:01:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Magicians? SOLO?</span><hr size=1> ok im a lvl 12 magician.  i have noticed that magicians can solo but not great, a druid and a nerco can solo better,  can anything else? a magician can solo one thing then med for about 5 min. i though people say magicians druids and necros could lvl so fast cause they can solo i think that is BS. cause a group you don't go OOM after one kill. please correct me if i am wrong? see i can only play about 2 hrs a night and at very random times and i don't want to play a necro. so with the times i play i need something that can solo deciant. what would you recomend. also i enjoy doing quest where i get items from and i notice magicians really don't have any quest.<br>
Tavaen <br>
Dark elf magician <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Insomnia</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/13/00 9:32:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ok</span><hr size=1> Umm, you don't really Know what your Talking About =) You are a &quot;Kewl Dood&quot; in the Making. But Anyway, if your Soloing Right, you shouldn't need 5 minutes to Med, cuz your not supposed to use all your mana (Duh). It should only take you 2-3 Bars of Mana to Kill Something. And a 5 minute Downtime is GREAT, Warriors a Few levels over you sit on their ass and Wait 20 minutes to fight again, at lvl13 or So, go to Ocean of Tears, and Kill Sisters, Great XPs. And BTW, Dark Elf Mages Rock =)<br>
Druids Solo Worse than you until lvl14. Necros, well, they're over Powered, get used to it, and you are Tied with Druids on Higher levels at solo, at your level, you are a Close third. Don't whine, develop Strategies =) And you'll Rock <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvylaek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vylaek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/14/00 4:09:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ok</span><hr size=1> Magicians are the second best solo class in the game, far better and more interesting solo than druids in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Necros are a better solo class overall, but against single spawns, Magicians can usually do them a level or two before a necro. <p>Vylaek, <BR>
Level 50 Dark Elf Magician<BR>
Pikka Chu, <BR>
Level 20 Ogre Warrior<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usvarinya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Svarinya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/14/00 4:59:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magicians? SOLO?</span><hr size=1> Not a good soloing class? bah you dont know how to play a mage. i watched a friend of mine go from 22 to 44 in 2 weeks with a mage. and my mage can solo fairly well. i just dont like to solo.<br>
<br>
Nendara Wylde<br>
Aegis Wolves<br>
&quot;When you need something summoned might as well summon something Wylde!&quot; <p><img src="http://www.wam.umd.edu/~brandysj/lee.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edano</A> at: 9/29/01 10:04:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Fuzze</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/14/00 5:16:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   We can solo</span><hr size=1> I think its abuncha BS that you think we CANT solo =) im one of the fastest levelers in my guild right now even faster than most of the druids and necro's and i only play 5 hours a day and weekends and have had no trouble leveling (until now at 45 bah) even now i can still get a good bubble of xp in 45 for ever 4 hours playing time which isnt bad at all.  You have to know WHERE to hunt as a magician..find the spots that nobody takes and that maybe do less damage for the same level of xp (like SF's and Aviak guards)...im level 45 almost ready to hit 46 in the next few days and i only have 19 played days to my name =) i know many druids that are 10 levels below me with 30 played days... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaginatakuroshio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naginata Kuroshio</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.rose-hulman.edu/~acuffnd/Reference/icon1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Elements</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/14/00 6:00:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We can solo</span><hr size=1> Can't solo?? I went from 39 to 44 in 10 days (and 40 to 44 in 4 as part of that).  I think that the previous poster is right - it's all about knowing where to hunt.<br>
<br>
On another note, if you're not on Quellious server, you may want to consider City of Mist for xp around 40 or so.  I get xp there in a group of 4 much faster than anywhere that I can solo... if you ARE on Quellious, stay outta my territory <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  - the yetis will be find for you until CoM goes green <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="mailto:naginata@magecompendium.com">Naginata Kuroshio, Master of the Elements</a><BR>
Magician of the 45th Circle<BR>
Phoenix Reborn<BR>
Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufactioner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Factioner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/14/00 10:12:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.castersrealm.com/images/Magician_bg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We can solo</span><hr size=1> Ok the one thing I see failed to mention here is where you are trying to solo. Ok a lvl 34 Magician is not going to solo a Hill Giant but a lvl 34 Druid might. You take that same Druid/Magician and put the in a dungeon and the Druid will die over and over again. Druids and were made to solo in the outdoors. They need the space to Kite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalysin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalysin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/15/00 9:07:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Magicians? SOLO?</span><hr size=1> You know, I am a fairly new mage too, and am coming to this board to do my homework on the class I have already fallen in love with.<br>
<br>
I see this post by another new mage like myself who is struggling to solo, and all you all do is bash him for saying he can't solo with his mage, and tell him he doesn't know how to play it and this and that.<br>
<br>
Then you post how easily you cruised up 20 levels in 2 weeks. Instead of bashng this guy for inquiring about your class, why not offer suggestions and places to hunt? Maybe a couple strategies? They don't have to be your secret hunting spots but just give a couple helpful hints instead of being so negative.<br>
<br>
Magician/Torv <p><fontcolor=black>
Kalysin</font>
<BR>Defender of Requim Despair
<BR>21st seasoned Warrior of Rallos

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Candela</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/15/00 11:42:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   No problems soloing</span><hr size=1> My magician at her level has been able to solo quite well and has lived  through some very scary fights.<br>
Surviving a fight against 2 Yellow /con Young kodiaks at once using a fire pet was quite a rush.<br>
I have a druid, necro, paladin and a wizard all in their 30's that have spent time soloing at different points in their lives. I would rate magicians as good as necromancers with druids coming in a close second.<br>
<br>
You can kill yellows/reds but I prefer killing multiple blues since you have more 'up time' and still get roughly the same amount of xp before you have to rest.<br>
<br>
Tavaen, it sounds like you want 'the best' and most powerful soloer from your post. I would recommend a necromancer for you. Personally I enjoy both.<br>
<br>
Candela<br>
11th Dark Elf Magician<br>
Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukassafehuhlume.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kassafeh Uhlume</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(8/16/00 1:21:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ::raises her hand::</span><hr size=1> Sweet!<br>
<br>
I haven't done much soloing since level 17 &amp; I miss it terribly.   High Keep is such a dreary DUNGEON.<br>
<br>
Can anyone give suggestions where Mages might find some good solitary hunting at various levels?   Currently I am 29 &amp; able to solo singleton gnolls in South Karana, but that's all I know of.<br>
<br>
